The year we made a baby, celebrating 2022 and 10 weeks until we meet our sweet little man ☘️

As many of you know, we are welcoming our first child in March 2023.  This is a humbling, human experience that we cannot fully anticipate how it will alter our lives/schedule.  In an attempt to have some personal boundaries, I have pre-selected my dates/locations this year for family portraits!  Each of these dates has both “petite” sessions that are 30 minutes + “full” sessions that are 60 minutes.  Full sessions are reserved for the “prime” golden hour time of the day and petite sessions will be earlier in the evening.  All times were selected to reflect the best light of the day! 

If you’re wanting to book an in-home, newborn or other session/location, please reach out to me directly!  I do have time and plans in my calendar to accomodate those!

Thank you for supporting my small business and my family — this is all possible because of you! 

*Link in bio for booking*

xo,
Cass

To see you become a mother — from the two years of trial and loss, to the first pregnancy test, through all the tests and procedures, the swollen belly and sleepless nights. The fluttery kicks and milkshakes. The 48 hours of labor, 4 hours of pushing. The arrival of a plump little man who was fascinated with you from the moment he was set on your chest and has continued to watch you with curiosity and amazement everyday since. To watch your heart expand. To see the pure, untethered joy when he smiles. To see the patience and empathy. To see you in his nose and eyes and gummy smile. To be a witness to this kind of love. The purest and truest joy of my life. The greatest honor to mother alongside my best friend. I love you, @enmurphy13 . You are the greatest gift of my life and I’ll thank my lucky stars every day that we gets to be yours. Happy Mothers Day, Mama.
